    # "Though this gave Sarah some space to breathe, the truth was that the five old houses held nearly as much power as all the other noble families combined."
    ""

translate ru VargaPath5_11df2eff:
    # "As a result, Rosanna had lost a great deal of its military power and the nation's economy had been thrown a state of disarray."
    ""

translate ru VargaPath5_c54332f1:
    # "The military reports slowly painted an increasingly clear picture."
    ""

translate ru VargaPath5_bc1bb58e:
    # "The old houses were gathering their forces near the western province of Dianthus, the ancestral seat of power of the Achillea family."
    ""

translate ru VargaPath5_d095fcfe:
    # "The borders of the province were carved out by a strong river, which made for a natural defence."
    ""

translate ru VargaPath5_ddbc7d32:
    # "The river also sprang from the neighbouring country of Normandi."
    ""

translate ru VargaPath5_76b1cfe3:
    # "As a result, not only was it impossible for Rosanna to cut off supplies to her enemy, in fact, it was her enemy who was now cutting off supplies to her."
    ""

translate ru VargaPath5_565c0694:
    # "Sarah had contacted the queen of Normandi, Queen Maeiv."
    ""

translate ru VargaPath5_a76f2f6c:
    # "Queen Maeiv ruled the neighbouring country of Normandi. Under her rule, the two countries had existed in a relative peace."
    ""

translate ru VargaPath5_7f34b323:
    # "This was not to say that their nations were allies, but they had managed to put their history of war to a rest."
    ""

translate ru VargaPath5_99d3feab:
    # "Sarah had urged her to block trade downstream from the river, preventing Marion's forces from being able to supply themselves."
    ""

translate ru VargaPath5_ecae3dcc:
    # "In truth, Sarah had asked her even more. She asked her to send an army to help her in crushing this rebellion, but as Sarah had expected, this demand was too much."
    ""

translate ru VargaPath5_e32981b7:
    # "Queen Maeiv agreed to block up the river, but refused to send her armies. She had offered up an excuse, but in truth, Sarah knew that she would receive no aid."
    ""

translate ru VargaPath5_d332674b:
    # "Sarah's position was still weak. She understood that Maeiv was simply refusing to commit herself to either side, so that she could be friendly with whichever side ended up winning."
    ""

translate ru VargaPath5_2ee06357:
    # "Still, with the river blocked up, Marion's troops would have a harder time to remain on the field."
    ""

translate ru VargaPath5_8049390a:
    # "Which also meant they would be more desperate to strike out before their supplies dwindled."
    ""

translate ru VargaPath5_e650a109:
    # "At every turn, Sarah saw the strategy shift and change. Each solution posed new problems."
    ""

translate ru VargaPath5_2f79fe5a:
    # "Sitting atop the throne, it was exactly such a new problem that came before Sarah."
